children.subject: They fall into the same category as EECS in the system.
For EE 16B, are there no seats reserved for CoE Undeclared students?

https://eecs.berkeley.edu/about/by-the-numbers 

In 2016 there were 1203 L&S juniors + seniors. The numbers keep increasing rapidly though.
Can't speak to the likelihood, but as stated above, we are working on it.
Approximately how many L&S CS majors are there for each year (thinking ~1000)? And what is the likelihood of the class getting expanded?
No, this exception was through Fall 2017, as widely advertised.
If we are graduating next semester, do we still have the option to replace 16a/16b by other courses as this semester?
Please see breakdown of seats above.

As a non-EECS CoE student, declaring CS double during the winter, do I have any reserved seats for 16B?
Indeed, I have successfully declared in the department but still waiting for the GPA of this semester in order to process the dual degree application.
For now, you may use Phase I to waitlist EE16B.
I'm a second year cs major. Can I use Phase 1 for EE16B or I can't enroll in Phase 1 at all?
Not at this time. Please see above.
Is there any seat in 16B reserved for non-EECS CoE students?
There are currently no seats for this category. If the class is expanded, it's possible a very small number of seats would be reserved for COE non-EECS, but you would likely be waitlisted.
So, if non-EECS CoE, should I phase 1 or phase 2 16b? Will I be on the waitlist regardless?
According to classes.berkeley.edu, there are currently 63 available seats for students like you. I would suggest phase 1
What's the recommended course of action for a L&S declared non-CS 2nd year trying to get into 16A?

It sounds like it's a new feature in the enrollment system to let students know when they are skipped on being processed from the waitlist.

Is there an enrollment category that you think you should qualify for? Otherwise, this looks just informational and nonactionable / telling you what you should already know via this post.
please see pinned post abt this email
Which pinned post? I had the same email.
What should I do if I got an email like this?
Please email me at ee-scheduling@eecs.berkeley.edu or lraya@berkeley.edu.
I am a L&S CS-intended transfer but when I tried to register for EE 16B. I was put on WaitList. Isn't there 35 seats reserved for us? Can someone help?
Your graduation date is irrelevant towards your enrollment priorities.
Gotcha. But does my senior standing mean I'd count as a senior or junior?

Ah, missed that part of your post.

Your standing is also irrelevant.

I'm an L&S CS major. On CalCentral it shows that I've had 5 terms in attendance meaning now, Fall 2017, is my 5th semester at Berkeley...which means this is my 3rd year aka junior year.

My graduation date, however, is Spring 2018 (I'm graduating in 3 years) and my standing is "Senior" on CalCentral. Does this mean I fall into the L&S CS 3rd year OR does it mean I fall into the L&S CS 4th year seat category in the system?
This is explained in the original post.
Are LSCS reserved for EE16B in Phase I?

Not sure if we spoke on the phone earlier. To clarify:

Some COE seats are reserved specifically for ME and Nuclear Eng, since those majors require EE16A. Going forward, ME students will take EE49 and will no longer have EE16A priority. Separately, there are 15 seats for broader COE majors such as Eng Physics.

For getting off the waitlist, does priority matter? For example if I am higher up on the waitlist (say 5), would someone who is lower (say 12) get chosen before during the adj. period because of priority?
If you don't meet the enrollment restrictions but a person below you does, then they will enroll: you not being able to enroll doesn't block other people from doing so.
And those enrollment requirements are that you need to take EE16A or Math 54 correct?
I'm not sure if I understand your question. The enrollment priorities are listed in the original post for both EE16A and 16B.

Are the "non-EECS CoE" spots reserved only for certain CoE majors (as listed on class schedule: http://classes.berkeley.edu/content/2018-spring-eleng-16a-001-lec-001)? I was placed on the waitlist (even when choosing open sections) even though I am a non-EECS CoE Major (Engineering Physics).
It was previously stated on this post that the department was looking into expanding EE 16B to ~800 seats. Also, there are 117 seats and 121 people on the waitlist and phase 2 hasn't started.
If the class is going to be expanded, it will be announced here. We're not intentionally withholding information from students.

Sorry I did not mean to imply that you were withholding information. I just wanted to know if there were still plans to expand the class so I could get an idea of whether I would get into it if I enroll during phase 2.

Please do not post here and also email the advisors. This is a major reason that we are not responding to Piazza posts any longer as it duplicates work.

This post will be updated when I know more about whether or not these classes expand.

Further EE enrollment questions should be directed to ee-scheduling@eecs.berkeley.edu.
Any news on whether EE16B will be expanded yet?

Hi there, 

If you are declared in another major, I do not believe Cal Central will let you access those seats.

If I am an applied math major and has already declare applied math. I  am also a new transfer student and I want to double in CS. Can I choose EE16A, just want to understand "L&S undeclared 1st years & new transfers - 175 seats". Is this also including a new transfer who has declared major?

history.content:
EE16A:

Update: We have expanded EE16A to 833 seats. The breakdown of seats is:

EECS (all years) - 75 seats 

L&S undeclared 1st years & new transfers - 175 seats

L&S undeclared 2nd & 3rd years - 150 seats

L&S CS 2nd years - 100 seats

L&S CS 3rd & 4th years - 225 seats

COE (majority are for ME juniors, a handful for Nuclear majors, 15 seats are for COE as a whole) majors - 81 seats

***Seats for L&S CS 3rd and 4th years will only be reserved through Phase I. They will be released on Oct 31 at 11:59PM.***

EE16B:

Update, 12/14: Nine new lab sections have been added; these have the letter "A" after the number, e.g. Lab 101A, 102A, etc. These new sections are being added to the existing lab sections, e.g. 101A corresponds with 101.

One "ghost" discussion section has been added, DIS 218. Students should choose DIS 218 to facilitate enrolling into the class, however you will actually attend a different section that works for your schedule.

In order to switch secondary sections while waitlisted, you must drop the class completely and re-add. This will put you at the bottom of the waitlist. Since we added enough seats for everyone, you will be enrolled once the waitlist processes automatically at 12:40AM, 6:40AM, 12:40PM, and 6:40PM every day as long as your sections are open and you do not have a time conflict. Please wait for the waitlist to run before responding to this email with questions.

If you have a time conflict, see instructions on EECS 101 Piazza post @5173.

We are working to expand the class to ~800 students. The current breakdown is prioritizing EECS majors and new L&S CS-intended students as EE16B is required for them once they declare:

L&S undeclared 1st years and transfers - 210 seats

EECS - 375 seats

We recommend that you use Phase I for either one of these classes.

**Please send questions to ee-scheduling@eecs.berkeley.edu. I am not going to respond to unique enrollment situations on Piazza.**

11/27: Unfortunately, I don't have an update at this time on expanding 16A either one of these classes. Unused reserved seats will expire at 11:59PM on 11/28 and the waitlist will be processed in order. Waitlisted students whose lab and/or discussion have filled will need to drop and re-add the class in order to switch to open sections. See @5173 if you have a time conflict w/ EE 16A or 16B (or other EE/EECS classes).
